{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Open Items Explicit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script reproduces and improves REAPER\u8217's media item's \u8220"double-click item\u8221" default action:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MIDI items \u8594 ? opened in the built-in MIDI editor (multi-selection consolidated automatically)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Audio items \u8594 ? opened in the Media Item Properties dialog (multi-selection consolidated automatically)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Subprojects \u8594 ? opened in new project tabs (multi-selection handled automatically by REAPER)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Unlike REAPER\u8217's native double-click behavior, this script:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Does not mess with current selection state\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can be assigned to any key, toolbar button, or controller\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Runs as efficiently as possible (no redundant loops or reselection)\sa180\par}
}

